doc.after: A gazetteer is a geographical dictionary or directory used in conjunction with a map or atlas 1 They typically contain information concerning the geographical makeup social statistics and physical features of a country region or continent Content of a gazetteer can include a subject s location dimensions of peaks and waterways population GDP and literacy rate This information is generally divided into topics with entries listed in alphabetical order
